  "prompt": "In Hurt Locker, how come Guy Pearce's character died due to the explosion despite all the padding and being outside the kill zone?",
  "response": "In \"The Hurt Locker,\" Guy Pearce's character, Sergeant Matt Thompson, is killed while disarming a bomb, which highlights the intense dangers faced by bomb disposal experts. Despite being outside the immediate blast radius and having protective gear, the explosion can still produce lethal effects due to the energy released, shrapnel, and the power of the blast wave. \n\nThe film portrays the reality of bomb disposal work, emphasizing that even with precautions, there is always a significant risk involved, especially with complex and unpredictable explosives. The tragic death of Thompson serves to underscore the perilous nature of their job and the high stakes that soldiers face in combat situations.",
